author: 75 years later, Japanese Americans recall pain of internment camps
title: U.S. carrier group patrols in South China Sea: U.S. navy
text:
U.S. carrier group patrols in South China Sea: U.S. navy Reuters 7 hrs ago Â© REUTERS/Mike Blake Sailors man the rails as the USS Carl Vinson aircraft carrier departs on deployment from Naval Station North Island in Coronado, California A United States aircraft carrier strike group has begun patrols in the South China Sea, the U.S. navy said on Saturday, amid renewed tension over the disputed waterway.
China's Foreign Ministry on Wednesday warned Washington against challenging its sovereignty, responding to reports the United States was planning fresh naval patrols in the South China Sea.
The navy said the force, including Nimitz-class aircraft carrier USS Carl Vinson, began routine operations in the South China Sea on Saturday. The announcement was posted on the Vinson's Facebook page.
(Reporting by Matthew Tostevin; Editing by Mary Milliken)
